item.title: Overclocking
item.dc:creator: @KeV KeV
item.description:
@KeV wrote:

Overclocking dramaticly reduces your PC’s life, making it not last as long. It will make your PC hotter than usual as your beefing up its reccommended default speed.

You can download overclocking programs or speed up your processorusing the BIOS (I tryed this once, and my monitor wouldn’t come on :S)

It’s not recommended, but it can be usefull for gaming.
